@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Main"
@prev "Requirements"
  Using MUICode
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  MUICode if far from being a complex software, and its use is quite
  simple. If you are familiar with Workbench, you don't really need 
  to read the following explanations to use MUICode

  For the others :
   
    The MUICode interface:
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~   
    The MUICode interface comprises three control pages and a list
    displaying the coded or decoded text.
   
    The first pages deals with files access, the second with text coding
    and decoding and the third enables to change the key (limited to five
    digits) used in the coding.
    
    How to code and decode:
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    To code a text file, you must perform the following operations:
       - provide a source text file name
       - provide a coding key
       - load the text file
       - start the coding by pressing the "Coding" button.

       Once a text has been coded, you can save it by providing a
       destination file name and pressing the "Save" button.
       
    Decode a text file, is as simple as the coding:
       - provide a source text file name
       - provide a coding key which must be the same that the one
         used to code the text
       - load the text file
       - start the decoding by pressing the "Decoding" button.
       
       You can save the decoded text by providing a destination file
       name and pressing the "Save" button.
       
    Acutally, the save button save the displayed text, which can be coded
    or not coded. 
          
    Furthermore, help bubbles will show off if you keep the mouse
    pointer still on an element of the interface, and the program will
    guide in the coding and decoding process with messages if you forget
    to perform a required step.

    NB: MUICode is quite slow; process a file bigger than 10ko can take
    a while, be patient !
@endnode

